Class Piece

  • java.lang.Object
    • duchess.logic.Piece
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Bishop, King, Knight, Pawn, Queen, Rook

    public abstract class Piece
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract class to represent all piece types in the game. Contains all of the shared functionality for the pieces.

      • findConsecutiveSquares

        protected java.util.ArrayList<Square> findConsecutiveSquares(int[][] modifiers,
                                                 int length)
        Finds all diagonal or orthogonal moves (Bishop, Rook, Queen & King). Modifiers is an array of four (x,y) pairs of "weights" which enable the same loop to be run for all four directions on the board. By choosing the modifiers accordingly, we get either diagonal or orthogonal consecutive squares. Length determines how many squares are explored at any direction (1 for king, 8 to others). Example of modifiers: see findDiagonalMoves() and findOrthogonalMoves()
        Parameters:
        modifiers - integer array of length [4][2]
        lenght - depth of exploration in squares
        Returns:
        ArrayList of squares containing legal moves

      • squaresToResolveCheck

        protected java.util.ArrayList<Square> squaresToResolveCheck(java.util.ArrayList<Square> moves)
        Find squares which resolve a check. When the game is in check, the only legal moves for pieces other than the king are those that are able to block the piece that is giving check.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        List of moves (Squares) that resolve the check
